  "body": "### Description\n\nI have following situation almost daily:\r\n* start a quarkus project by running mvn clean compile quarkus:dev\r\n* fails, because my docker daemon is not auto starting on boot of my pc.\r\n* start docker\r\n* press s in quarkus terminal to force restart\r\n* fails.\r\n\r\nIt seems like the docker daemon is only searched for on initial boot, but not on hot reload.\r\nCould quarkus also search for the daemon on hot reload, when following conditions are true?\r\n- quarkus requires docker (e.g. for dev services)\r\n- and no daemon was found on initial dev mode start\r\n\r\n\r\nThis would at least allow dev mode to run, and prevent the need to do a full restart.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
